    "For both frames, assume that the accessibility relation R i is the universal relation.Proposition 5.53 (Preservation under Selective Subframes).",
    "If F ′ is a selective subframe of a possibility frame F, then:1.",
    "F ′ is a possibility frame; 2. if F is full, then F ′ is full; 3. for all φ ∈ L(Φ, I), F ⊩ φ implies F ′ ⊩ φ.Proof.",
    "For part 1, we must first show that P ′ is closed under the operations ∩, ⊃ ′, and ■ ′ i as in Definition 2.1, and ∅ ∈ P ′.",
    "Since ∅ ∈ P, we have ∅ = ∅ ∩ S ′ ∈ P ′ by Definition 5.52.2."
  ]
}